The paper proposes a mechanism for distributing applications across the Cloud and the Fog using deep Q-networks, which is a type of reinforcement learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to distributed computing, resource allocation, and optimization, which are relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the trade-off between QoS and running costs, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
